article.headline: Baylor 90, Alcorn State 59
article.story: WACO, Texas (AP) -- Aaron Bruce scored 20 points, 17 of them in the second half, to lead Baylor to a 90-59 win over Alcorn State on Monday night. Curtis Jerrells added 16 points, while Tim Bush contributed 14 and Henry Dugat 11 for the Bears (4-1). Baylor connected on 13 of its 29 3-point attempts with Bruce hitting 6 of 9. The Bears moved in front 52-27 with seven straight points to open the second half and coasted to the win. Alex Owumi led Alcorn State (0-6) with 12 points, and Clifton Douglass added 10. Baylor outshot the Braves 57 percent (35-of-61) to 34 percent (19-of-56) from the field. The Bears also grabbed 43 rebounds to Alcorn State's 29 and dominated the Braves in the paint, outscoring them 40-22. Trailing 7-4, the Bears went on a 14-3 run and took an 18-10 lead midway through the first half. Baylor used a 13-2 run late in the first half to extend its lead to 39-20. Jerrells' 11-first half points propelled the Bears to a 45-27 margin at the half.
